What B2B intent-based marketing really means

B2B intent-based marketing is the practice of using behavioral data to understand which companies are actively researching products or services related to your offerings. These behaviors may include:

• Reading industry articles
• Downloading whitepapers or reports
• Searching for solution-specific keywords
• Engaging with competitor content
• Visiting relevant review or comparison pages

Intent data goes beyond basic demographics or firmographics. It answers a critical question: “Who is in-market right now?”

For US businesses operating in competitive markets like SaaS, cybersecurity, healthcare tech, fintech, or manufacturing, this shift from volume-based marketing to intent-driven precision is essential.

Why intent data matters more than ever in 2026

Today’s B2B buyers are up to 70% through their decision-making process before they ever speak to a sales representative. This trend has continued into 2026 as self-service research and peer validation dominate buying journeys.

Intent data allows marketing and sales teams to:

