Different types of B2B intent data you should know

Not all intent data is the same. Understanding the types helps you use it more effectively.

First-party intent data
This comes from your owned digital properties such as:

• Website visits
• Content downloads
• Email engagement
• Webinar attendance

Second-party intent data
This is shared data from trusted partners, publishers, or platforms where your audience engages.

Third-party intent data
Collected from external networks that monitor content consumption, searches, and interactions across the web.

A strong intent-based marketing program combines all three, enriched with AI and analytics to create accurate buying-stage insights.

Intent-based marketing works best with ABM

Account-based marketing and intent data are naturally connected. ABM focuses on targeting specific high-value accounts, while intent data tells you which of those accounts are actively researching.

When combined, you can:

